node.text: Such a beautiful photo 🧡  love the dress
Such a cute look 🧡🧡

Last day of Circuit Breaker here in Singapore and while that doesn’t mean stores or restaurants are open it does mean the kids can go back to school for their last week. .
.
.
Celebrating the small victories where I can because there is so much hurt in the world right now. Also, trying to do my part to raise my kids to spread joy and love, to think before they speak, and to think through all the levels of their actions before they do them. Simple lessons really but sometimes simple things can bring great change. .
.
.
Dress @daily_sleeper 
Necklaces @lionetteny 
Glasses @aliexpress
Loving the colour on you 😍

It’s actually a mammoth task to keep kids uplifted and on track during all of this. We will probably look back in amazement at what we managed to achieve through it all.  Stay 💪💕
The simplest things can have the most impact. 😊
Whooohooo bring on school tomorrow. Love these snaps. It’s been fun seeing all our CB posts. Love the little feet popping out.
Most glam/fun momma I know. 💛
Cant wait for the normalcy to resume😍
@thepinklotushk hurrah for small gains
We’ve got to take joy in the small victories.
@bhangrababies thank you. Always close by for sure!
Hahaha, I love the extra set of feet in the last image. You look gorgeous, like always ❤️❤️
@florencesorgini slow down there! One kid goes this week and the other goes next week. So not quiet silent but a reduced decibel level.
It’s time to party!!! Make a glass of tea and enjoy the silence:)
